<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 08 at 3:20PM CDT  by NWS Shreveport</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Panola,
southeastern Rusk and northwestern Shelby Counties through 345 PM
CDT...
At 319 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles south of Pinehill, or 17 miles southwest of Carthage, moving
northeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Carthage, Gary City, Woods, Lawsonville and Dotson.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
